We should reduce carbon dioxide emissions; we should reduce our dependency on imports and increase the degree to which we are self-sufficient in Europe; we should not be as easily affected by energy crises in other parts of the world; 
          and
        , by promoting renewable energy sources, we should provide incentives for innovation and technical development within this area which, in turn, would lead to further cleaner and more efficient energy consumption.

Without the certainty of possible growth there will be no investment and no research; 

            in short

        , there will not be that kind of concentration of resources and energies that will enable the sector to make a qualitative leap.

